DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
);

Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$r = random(3,5,1);
$r1 = $r - 1;
$a = 1;
$b = 2**$r;

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Use the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus to find

$PAR
\(\int_{$a}^{$b}\,\frac{e^{\root $r\of{x}}}{\root $r\of{x^{$r1}}}\,dx = \)
\{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( num_cmp( "$r*e*(e-1)" ) );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

We use substitution with \(w = \root $r\of{x} = x^{1/$r}\).  Then 
\(w(1) = 1\) and \(w($b) = 2\), and
\(dw = {1\over $r}\,x^{(1/$r) - 1}\, dx = {1\over $r\,x^{$r1/$r}}\, dx\).
Recognizing that \(x^{$r1/$r} = \root $r\of{x^{$r1}}\), we have
\[
  \int_{$a}^{$b}\,\frac{e^{\root $r\of{x}}}{\root $r\of{x^{$r1}}}\,dx =
  $r \int_{1}^{2}\,e^{w}\,dw = $r\,e^{w}\bigg|_{1}^{2} = 
  $r (e^2 - e).
\]

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

ENDDOCUMENT();
